result.execSummary:
The defendant Kayla Marie DREWS was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misappropriate ID Info - Avoid Penalty, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by the Department of Corrections.

Submit to random urine screens and pay for same.

Maintain absolute sobriety.

Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process.

No direct or indirect contact with Justin Eisenschink except with the permission of the agent.

No contact with Spud's Bar, Ripley's Bar, Seven Lakes, Branch River's Edge, Knox's Silver Valley, Great Escape, Schmitz Amusement, Timeout Sports Bar.

No possession or use of alcohol, illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.

No entry to any place where these items are sold or used.  That includes bars, taverns and liquor stores.

Any prescriptions from a doctor and any over the counter medication should be taken only as directed.

No contact with Leah Truettner.
